column34:
- fundamentals (ball control, passing, defending)
- physical reactivity

- better decision making when in control of the ball. When not passing quickly, he sometimes becomes predictable with the ball. So maybe pass the ball or attempt a play a bit quicker?
- positioning when not on the ball. Even in drills, eg rondos, he will not position himself optimally (ie in the line of passing but away from the passer).
- positioning again, but defensively. He'll sometimes move away from his formation (often towards the center positions) and might engage in pressing that leaves the team in men inferiority (ie when pressing a man already covered, therefore leaving an opponent free to receive the ball)
